<item>
            <title>[LU-7502] add lfs find --mdt-count and --mdt-hash options</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7502</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There should be options for &lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe&lt;/tt&gt; to use &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;count&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;hash&lt;/tt&gt; options for &lt;tt&gt;lfs find&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe&lt;/tt&gt; to return the striped directory stripe count and directory hash function respectively. There isn&apos;t a good short option for &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;count&lt;/tt&gt;, since &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;M&lt;/tt&gt; is already used for mtime.  While &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;mdt&amp;#45;hash&lt;/tt&gt; could use &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;H&lt;/tt&gt;, it isn&apos;t clear that this is an option that will be used enough to justify having a short option.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
